parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the ABS light illuminates
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes lock up
the vehicle does not stop quickly
or the brakes fail to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the inability to stop the vehicle in a timely manner.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
or the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause brake failure, accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes do not engage
or the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Leading to Loss of Power and Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the engine can cause a loss of power, leading to a loss of control, and potentially result in accidents or fires, which can pose a significant risk to the safety of the occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Clunking noise
smoke emanating from the vehicle
loss of power
engine failure
vehicle catching on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Intermittent ABS system failure
pedal goes to the floor
extended stopping distance
alignment issues in the front end.
